4 Sec. 14. (1) The MIDC shall not make a grant under section 13
5 unless the indigent defense system has an approved plan and cost
6 analysis under section 13(4).
7 (2) The first MIDC grant installment to an indigent defense
8 system is 40% of the system's grant award. The 3 subsequent MIDC
9 grant installments are each 20% of the indigent defense system's
10 grant award.
11 (3) After the first grant installment under subsection (2),
12 the 3 subsequent grant installments are based on the MIDC's review
13 and approval of documentation provided to the MIDC by the indigent
14 defense system, including documentation of expenditures and
15 unexpended funds under section 13(14) and (15). The indigent
16 defense system's documented expenditures for the prior quarter must
17 be not less than 25% of the total plan and cost analysis approved
18 under section 13(4).
19 (4) The MIDC may allow an indigent defense system to request
20 to be exempt from the requirements under this section for
21 unforeseeable conditions that may prohibit timely expenditure
22 processing by the system.
23 Sec. 15. (1) Except as provided in section 5, if a dispute
24 arises between the MIDC and an indigent criminal defense system
25 concerning the requirements of this act, including a dispute
26 concerning the approval of an indigent criminal defense system's
27 annual plan , or cost analysis, or compliance with section 13 or
28 17, the parties shall attempt to resolve the dispute by mediation.
29 The state court administrator, as authorized by the supreme court,
